<https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/treasure-valuation-committee> <http://ogp.me/ns#description> "The Treasure Valuation Committee (TVC), comprising of independent antiques or coin experts and a representative of the hobby of metal-detecting, establishes the likely market value of each treasure find. A reward of this value can then be made to the finders of treasure and to the owners of find sites unless there are grounds for no reward or a reduced award to be made. TVC is an advisory non-departmental public body, sponsored by the Department for Culture, Media and Sport ."@en <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/rdfa> .
